Franklin.Rainey House (Franklin, Tennessee):
The Rainey House is a one-and-a-half-story stone cottage in Franklin, Tennessee that dates from 1839, was present at the American Civil War battles of Franklin, and was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1970. It has also been known as The Bob Rainey House.
When listed the property included two contributing buildings on an area of 9.9 acres (4.0 ha).
